\begin {tikzcd}
  \Delta \ar [rr, hookrightarrow, "y"]\ar [ddrr, "F"', bend right] &&
  \textsc {sSet}\ar [dd, "\operatorname *{Lan}_y F"',
  bend right] \\
  && \dashv  \\
  && E\ar [uu, "{E(F-, -)}"', bend right]\makebox [0pt][l]{.}
\end {tikzcd}

fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
Let C\xrightarrow {F}Set be any functor. Then the projection functor \text {el}(F)\xrightarrow {\Pi } C from the category of elements strictly creates:
all limits that C admits and F preserves;
all connected colimits that C admits.

Let C\xrightarrow {F} D be a functor with C small and D
complete. Then there is an equalizer diagram





    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
