  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [rr, "F", ""' {name=F}]\ar [dr, "K"'] && E\ar [r, "L"] & F\\
    & D\ar [ur, "\operatorname *{Lan}_K F"']
    \ar [from=F, to=2-2, Rightarrow, "\eta "]
  \end {tikzcd}$\cong $
  \begin {tikzcd}
    C\ar [r, "F"]\ar [dr, "K"'] & E\ar [r, "L"] & F\\
    & D\ar [ur, "\operatorname *{Lan}_K LF"']
    \ar [from=1-2, to=2-2, Rightarrow]
  \end {tikzcd},


 i.e. if the Kan extension of LF along K is naturally
isomorphic to the whiskered composite of \eta  by L.

Explicitly, a left Kan extension consists of a functor D\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{Lan}_K} F together with a
  natural transformation F\xrightarrow {\eta } (\operatorname *{Lan}_K F)K, as in 




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
