 such that the two squares involving the left and right adjoints, respectively,
commute, and satisfying any of the following equivalent conditions:

Let F: C\rightleftarrows  D: G be a pair of opposing functors
equipped with isomorphisms D(Fc, d)\cong  C(c, Gd) for every c\in  C and
d\in  D. Then this data forms an adjunction, and in particular these
isomorphisms are natural, if and only if, for
every quadruple of morphisms as in the following display, the left-hand square
commutes if and only if the right-hand square commutes:




    \usepackage{tikz, tikz-cd, mathtools, amssymb}
  \usetikzlibrary{shapes.geometric}
  \usetikzlibrary{calc}
  \usetikzlibrary{matrix}
  \usetikzlibrary{decorations.markings}

  \tikzset{
    % basics
    square/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=4},
    triangle/.style={draw, regular polygon, regular polygon sides=3},
  }

  \tikzset{
