    \begin {tikzcd}
    \operatorname *{lim}_J F\ar [dr, "\operatorname *{lim}_J \alpha "']\ar [r] & F\ar [r, "\alpha "] & G \\
    & \operatorname *{lim}_J G\ar [ur]
    \end {tikzcd}


 The first map defines the action of \operatorname *{lim}_J on
  \alpha .

To see that this defines a functor, given two natural transformations
  F\xrightarrow {\alpha }G\xrightarrow {\beta } H, observe that the map \operatorname *{lim}_J   F\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{lim}_J\alpha }\operatorname *{lim}_J G\xrightarrow {\operatorname *{lim}_J\beta }\operatorname *{lim}_J H 
  factors the cone \operatorname *{lim}_J F\to  F\to  G\to  H:





